</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="178" pageNumber="457" type="breeding">
<paragraph blockId="178.[1448,2655,1670,2452]" pageId="178" pageNumber="457">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1449,1584,2181,2214]" pageId="178" pageNumber="457">Breeding.</emphasis>
In Choc6, Colombia, reproductively active Dusky Rice Rats were recorded in March; a pregnant female gave birth to two young.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1448,2150,2261,2294]" pageId="178" pageNumber="457" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="178.[1448,2655,1670,2452]" box="[1448,2150,2261,2294]" pageId="178" pageNumber="457">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1448,1683,2261,2294]" pageId="178" pageNumber="457">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
The Dusky Rice Ratis terrestrial.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
